The 2015–16 Ekstraklasa is the 60th season of the Ekstraklasa, Polish's top-tier handball league. A total of twelve teams contest this season's league, which begins on 2 September 2015 and is scheduled to conclude in May 2016.
Vive Tauron Kielce are the defending champions.


== Team information ==

The following 12 clubs compete in the Ekstraklasa during the 2015–16 season:


== Regular season ==
A victory over a team in full-time added two points, a draw added one point and a loss added no points.


